fields.name: Air Filter
fields.description: Filters air entering the engine for combustion.

fields.name: Brake Pad
fields.description: Applies pressure to brake rotors to slow the vehicle.

fields.name: Spark Plug
fields.description: Ignites fuel-air mixture in engine cylinders.

fields.name: Fuel Filter
fields.description: Filters impurities from fuel before it reaches the engine.

fields.name: Timing Belt
fields.description: Synchronizes the rotation of engine components.

fields.name: Battery
fields.description: Provides electrical power to start the engine.

fields.name: Alternator
fields.description: Generates electricity to charge the battery and power the vehicle.

fields.name: Radiator
fields.description: Cools engine coolant to prevent overheating.

fields.name: Water Pump
fields.description: Circulates coolant through the engine and radiator.
